). Remaining antennal segments 45, length of antenna 1.7 times fore wing, length of third segment 1.3 times fourth, length of third, fourth and penultimate segments 4, 3 and 2.2 times their maximal width, flagellomeres with two ranks of placodes, apical segment 2.4 times its maximal width; eyes sparsely setose; length of eye in dorsal view 1.6 times temple; temple directly narrowed posteriorly, punctate, weakly coriaceous ventrally and smooth dorsally, shiny (
figure 1
