Mesosoma
(
figure 73
). Length of mesosoma 1.5 times its maximal height; side of pronotum medially rugose, basally coriaceous and remainder smooth; mesopleuron punctate, smooth and shiny; precoxal sulcus distinctly punctate, not reaching anterior margin of mesopleuron; metapleuron finely punctate; mesoscutum sparsely punctate; scutellar sulcus narrow with small carinae; scutellum convex; propodeum convex in lateral view, smooth and punctate with some weak transverse vermiculous rugae medially (
